## Weapon Proficiency Display

### Overview
Implement dynamic proficiency indication on weapon sheets that checks if the viewing actor has the required Weapon Training talent.

### User Story
As a player viewing a weapon, I want to immediately see if my character can use it proficiently, so I know if I'll suffer penalties.

### Concept
- Weapon specifies required training (e.g., 'Weapon Training (Las)')
- When viewed by actor, system checks for matching talent
- Visual indicator: ✓ Proficient / ✗ Untrained / ⚠ Partial

### Data Model Changes

**Weapon Schema Addition:**
```javascript
// Already exists but unused - repurpose
proficiency: new fields.StringField({
    required: false,
    blank: true,
    label: 'Required Training'
}),

// Or more structured:
requiredTraining: new fields.SchemaField({
    talentName: new fields.StringField({ initial: 'Weapon Training' }),
    specialization: new fields.StringField({ initial: '' }), // 'Las', 'Bolt', etc.
})
```

**WeaponData Getter:**
```javascript
/**
 * Check if an actor has proficiency with this weapon.
 * @param {Actor} actor - The actor to check
 * @returns {object} { proficient: boolean, partial: boolean, message: string }
 */
checkProficiency(actor) {
    if (!this.requiredTraining?.specialization) {
        return { proficient: true, partial: false, message: 'No training required' };
    }

    const talentName = this.requiredTraining.talentName;
    const spec = this.requiredTraining.specialization;

    // Find Weapon Training talent with matching specialization
    const talent = actor.items.find(i => 
        i.type === 'talent' &&
        i.system.identifier === 'weapon-training' &&
        i.system.specialization === spec
    );

    if (talent) {
        return { proficient: true, partial: false, message: `Trained: ${talentName} (${spec})` };
    }

    // Check for universal training
    const universal = actor.items.find(i =>
        i.type === 'talent' &&
        i.system.identifier === 'weapon-training' &&
        i.system.specialization === 'Universal'
    );

    if (universal) {
        return { proficient: true, partial: true, message: 'Universal training applies' };
    }

    return { 
        proficient: false, 
        partial: false, 
        message: `Missing: ${talentName} (${spec})` 
    };
}
```

### Sheet Display

**Header Badge:**
```handlebars
{{#if viewingActor}}
<span class='rt-proficiency-badge rt-proficiency-badge--{{proficiencyStatus.class}}'
      data-tooltip='{{proficiencyStatus.message}}'>
    {{#if proficiencyStatus.proficient}}
    <i class='fa-solid fa-check-circle'></i> Proficient
    {{else}}
    <i class='fa-solid fa-times-circle'></i> Untrained (-20)
    {{/if}}
</span>
{{/if}}
```

**Visual States:**
- **Proficient (green)**: ✓ character has Weapon Training (X)
- **Universal (blue)**: ~ character has Universal training
- **Untrained (red)**: ✗ character lacks required talent, shows penalty

### Context Requirements
Sheet needs to know which actor is viewing:
```javascript
// In _prepareContext
if (this.item.actor) {
    context.viewingActor = this.item.actor;
    context.proficiencyStatus = this.item.system.checkProficiency(this.item.actor);
}
```

### Pack Data Update
Populate `requiredTraining` for all 1,093 weapons based on type:
- Las weapons -> 'Weapon Training (Las)'
- Bolt weapons -> 'Weapon Training (Bolt)'
- Melee primitive -> 'Weapon Training (Primitive)'
- etc.

### GM Permission System (Future Extension)
- GM setting to allow/disallow player editing of weapons
- Permission levels: View Only, Edit Stats, Full Edit
- Separate ticket for this feature

### Dependencies
- Depends on RogueTraderVTT-6zd (Data Model Rework) for proficiency field decision
- Depends on RogueTraderVTT-viw (Sheet Redesign) for display integration

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Weapon specifies required training
- [ ] Sheet shows proficiency status when viewed by actor
- [ ] Visual distinction between proficient/untrained
- [ ] Tooltip explains proficiency status
- [ ] Works with Universal training fallback
- [ ] Pack data populated with correct training requirements
